s which might occur as a result of concentrated fishing in sensitive areas or climate change. Frequent assessment of the krill stock will enhance CCAMLR's ability to manage these risks. Continuing the local monitoring programs will provide valuable information on krill variability, but more information is required on how the monitored biomass relates to biomass at the subarea and regional scales.},
author = {Hill, S. L. and Atkinson, A. and Darby, C. and Fielding, S. and Krafft, B. A. and God{\o}, O. R. and Skaret, G. and Trathan, P. N. and Watkins, J. L.},
